@page
@model newhorizonmission_asp.net.Pages.AboutRoss.RossInShortModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Ross";
}

<div class="jumbotron w3-container w3-center w3-animate-bottom">
    <h1 class="display-4">About Me</h1>
    <div id="carouselExampleIndicators" class="carousel slide title_image" data-ride="carousel">
        <ol class="carousel-indicators">
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="1"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="2"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="3"></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img class="d-block w-100" src="~/images/me_04.jpg" alt="First slide">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img class="d-block w-100" src="~/images/me_01.jpg" alt="Second slide">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img class="d-block w-100" src="~/images/me_02.jpg" alt="Second slide">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img class="d-block w-100" src="~/images/me_03.jpeg" alt="Third slide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
        </a>
    </div>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p class="lead">
        I grew up here in the lower mainland, first in Richmond, and then in the Surrey/Delta area.
        I then spent a decade or so in the Okanagan, where I obained a bachelor's degree in psychology with a
        minor in philosophy. Following this I spent several years writing science fiction books, and then later
        got into the CST program at BCIT, from which I have now graduated.
    </p>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p class="lead">
        I've always been a big techie; I've always been interested in hardware and how things work.
        I've always enjoyed using cool technology, as well as curiuos about what goes on under the hood, and
        what makes it all go. Going to BCIT for software development was a bit of a gamble, but it's paying off.
        I think I've taken to it very well though. I really enjoy the work and am find the content compelling.
        I'm so eager to hit the ground and get to work!
    </p>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p class="lead">
        More personally, I'm a lifelong learner and am always trying to learn everything about
        everything. I have an 800 hour backlog podcast playlist, I enjoy running and would like to run a
        marathon some day. I enjoy video games; I'm a Nintendo boy for life but I also love my PS4 now. I love
        science fiction and comedy, especially put together! Good compelling drama is wonderful as well of
        course.
    </p>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p class="lead">
        I DO exist on social media! You can find me on <a href="https://twitter.com/wrosswhite"><u>twitter</u></a>, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/williamrosswhite"><u>instagram</u></a>, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/wrosswhite"><u>LinkedIn</u></a>, and <a href="https://github.com/williamrosswhite"><u>github</u></a>
    </p>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <p class="lead"></p>
</div>

